				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I love robert jordan, he rocks, too bad new books are so slow to be published hehe.
<br />

<br />
My favorite part in the Goodkind series was when Richard was captured and tortured by that lady, foget her name.  With that club thing she used to beat him and drive him to the brink of madness, i liked that whole section of the book.  
<br />

<br />
Tad Williams series starting with the Dragonbone chair is a good one that i enjoyed. Memory , sorrow, and thorn is the name of the series, its about 4 good size books long.
<br />
<a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/stores/series/-/131/mass_market/ref=ref=pd_sim_series/102-2153460-1676164" target="_blank">http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/stores/series/-/131/mass_market/ref=ref=pd_sim_series/102-2153460-1676164</a>
<br />

<br />
One of my absolute favorites is C.S. Friedmans series  Coldfire trilogy, omg this book surprised me.  THIS IS A MUST READ!! The way the author twists the lines between good and evil.  ITs fantasy with a nice sci fi twist.  Very good find i must say
<br />
<a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0886775272/qid=1042654691/sr=8-1/ref=sr_8_1/102-2153460-1676164?v=glance&s=books&n=507846" target="_blank">http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/tg/detail/-/0886775272/qid=1042654691/sr=8-1/ref=sr_8_1/102-2153460-1676164?v=glance&s=books&n=507846</a>
<br />

<br />
Michael moorcocks eternal champion series is very good too if you like that kind of sci-fi fantasy.
<br />

<br />
Dennis L Mckienrnans Book "Eye of the hunter" was a very good read, wishy i can say the same for alot of his other books, but most of his others are too predictable and Tolkien-esk.
<br />

<br />
This one is also very good
<br />
<a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0886776686/qid=1042654940/sr=2-3/ref=sr_2_3/102-2153460-1676164" target="_blank">http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0886776686/qid=1042654940/sr=2-3/ref=sr_2_3/102-2153460-1676164</a>
