			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I love reading Fantasy books. I have an entire bookcase full of them.
<br />

<br />
Terry Goodkind - By no means is it bad writing, but it isn't my style
<br />

<br />
Robert Jordan - Good stuff, only have the first 3 Wheel of Time books
<br />

<br />
Weis + Hickman - Dragonlance books, I have every single one (over 120 books), of course not all written by Weis and Hickman, but based on their world. Great stuff, pick them up if you like Forgotten Realms. Their Well of Darkness trilogy (last book out soon) is also really creative and well written.
<br />

<br />
But my personal favorite, C.S. Friedman. He wrote the Black Sun Rising trilogy, probably the most creative, interesting, and just plain great books I've ever read.<br />_________________<br />"History is just a set of lies agreed upon"
<br />

<br />
- Napoleon</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
